:Antigone_Character_Fates
a :Character ;
:role "Deities of Destiny"^^xsd:string ;
:description "The Moirai, who control the destiny of mortals and gods alike."^^xsd:string .

################################################################

# THEMES, MOTIVATIONS, EMOTIONS, MYTHS

################################################################

:Theme_FateInevitability
a :Theme ;
:description "The inescapable nature of Fate (Moirai), which catches even those of divine birth."^^xsd:string .

:Theme_NobleSuffering
a :Theme ;
:description "The recurring motif of high-born or divine figures enduring horrific pain and imprisonment."^^xsd:string .

:Motivation_ContextualizeSuffering
a :Motivation ;
:description "To comfort or warn Antigone by showing that even the gods' children suffer cruel fates."^^xsd:string .

:Emotion_Agony
a :Emotion ;
:description "Physical and mental suffering caused by blinding and imprisonment."^^xsd:string .

:Emotion_Despair
a :Emotion ;
:description "The misery of wasting away ('melting away') in an unfortunate plight."^^xsd:string .

:Emotion_VengefulRage
a :Emotion ;
:description "Implicit scream for vengeance against the savage injustice."^^xsd:string .

:Myth_PhineusSons
a :MythologicalBackground ;
:description "The blinding of Phineus' sons by their stepmother in Thrace."^^xsd:string .

:Myth_CleopatraBoread
a :MythologicalBackground ;
:description "The story of Cleopatra, daughter of the North Wind, who despite her divine speed and origin, was trapped by Fate."^^xsd:string .

:Conflict_FateVsDivinity
a :Conflict ;
:description "The conflict between divine heritage and the superior power of Fate."^^xsd:string ;
:conflictBetween :Antigone_Character_Cleopatra, :Antigone_Character_Fates .

:Fate_CleopatraDoom
a :FateConcept ;
:description "The eternal Fates descending upon the child of Boreas."^^xsd:string .
